==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nematoidea
<hw>Nem`a*toi"de*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>nh^ma</grk>, <grk>nh`matos</grk>, thread +
<ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A phylum of worms,
having a long, round, and generally smooth body; the roundworms. Called
also <altname>Nematodea</altname>, and more commonly
<altname>Nematoda</altname>. Formerly, it was classed as a taxonomic
order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The trichina, stomach worm, and pinworm of man belong to
this group. See also <cref>Vinegar eel</cref>, under <er>Vinegar</er>,
and <er>Gapeworm</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nematoidean</ent>⟦br⟧
